<h2 class="section_title">&mdash; <%= t('.pricing') %> &mdash;</h2>

<section class="pricing">
<div class="inner">

  <ul>
    <li>
    <a href="#"><h3>Why is the price an approximation? How will I know the final price for my map?</h3></a>
    <p>Since data sets are formatted differently we first have to analyze if the data need to be cleaned or not, or if we will have to do more than expected data manipulation to render it properly on a map. As such we can only offer an approximation at the beginning.</p>

<p>Once our team of data experts finish analyzing your data we will send an email to the address you provided with your inquiry with the final cost breakdown.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
    <a href="#"><h3>If MaaS hosts my map, for how long will it work? </h3></a>
    <p>We will host your map for an indefinite period of time, and since we host in the cloud you can be certain that your maps will scale no matter what your traffic requirements become. </p>
    </li>
    <li>
    <a href="#"><h3>Are there any periodic quotas for the hosting?</h3></a>
    <p>No, there are no periodic hosting quotas with MaaS. Your maps are hosted on our servers free of charge for as long as you may need them.</p>
    <p>This does not apply to excessive use which is determined at two million requests (tiles or data requests), including, but not limited to, requests that result from Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attacks, within a thirty day period will be considered Excessive Use. You may be responsible for additional fees for Excessive Use.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
    <a href="#"><h3>What payment methods does MaaS accept?</h3></a>
    <p>We accept all major credit cards including MasterCard, Visa, Maestro, AmEx and Discover. If you’re in the United States or Canada, tax is included, for European clients, VAT is included in the price of each MaaS project.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
    <a href="#"><h3>Can I get a discount?</h3></a>
    <p>Please get in touch with us for volume orders, dedicated CartoDB instances, and large cartography, citizen science, journalism, geocoding, GIS, or similar projects.</p>
    </li>
  </ul>

</div>

</section>

